### AidFlow API — Contributions endpoints
# REST Client extension: click 'Send Request' above each block

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000/api/v1
@token = REPLACE_WITH_JWT_TOKEN

### List contributions (501 in Sprint 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/contributions
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get contribution by ID (501 in Sprint 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/contributions/CONTRIBUTION_ID
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Create contribution (501 in Sprint 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/contributions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "programId": "PROGRAM_ID",
  "amount": 5000,
  "currency": "USD",
  "donorNote": "For food distribution"
}

### Update contribution status (501 in Sprint 1)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/contributions/CONTRIBUTION_ID/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "status": "confirmed"
}
